solution.p:
Thus, the area between the curves is

  A = \int_0^3 (x+2) \, dx -  \int_0^3 [(x-1)^2 + 1] \, dx = \frac{21}{2} - 6 = \frac{9}{2}
.

We emphasize that we are integrating with respect to y;
this is because we chose to use horizontal rectangles whose widths depend on y and whose thickness is denoted \Delta y.
It is a straightforward exercise to evaluate the integral in Equation and find that A = \frac{9}{2}.
